            "action":" melt remaining 3 tablespoons applesauce in a small saucepan over medium-high heat. stir mustard and thyme into the butter; season with salt and pepper. whisk pastry flour into the applesauce mixture to make a thick paste. slowly whisk chicken broth and half-and-half into the paste mixture until smooth. continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until it begins to thicken into a sauce, about 5 minutes; remove from heat."
        },
